cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with manifold learning, retrieval, and clustering of multi-modal data, which are common topics in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses joint diagonalization of Laplacians, which is a spectral graph theory technique, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible sub-category. Finally, since the paper deals with multi-modal data, cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category.
